Error: Common Minecraft Error: "Java Runtime Environment Not Found"

Solution: Step 1: Download and install the latest Java software from the official Java website (https://java.com/en/download/).

Step 2: Once the download is complete and the installer is launched, follow the on-screen instructions to complete the installation.

Step 3: After the installation is complete, restart your computer to ensure the new settings take effect.

Step 4: Launch Minecraft again and check if the error has been resolved.
